abstract: CLIFTON, N.J., May 14 Nobody has ever accused Nancy Lopez-Melton of having a perfect golf swing. For the last two years, though, she had the most effective one on the Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour.
headline_main: Mrs. Melton Looks For Her Old Swing; Help on the Way In Right Rhythm Moser Retains Dodge Open Lead

abstract: Jose Amy, a 26 year-old jockey, said yesterday in Brooklyn Federal Court that he lied to a grand jury last December about three of the several dozen races that he had said Con Errico tried to fix in 1974 and 1975.
headline_main: Amy Says He Lied to Grand Jury on Fixes; Knew He Was Lying Went Back to Grand Jury Amy Admits Lying on Fixes

abstract: Jose Amy, a jockey whose horse earned more than $2 million last year. implicated some of the nation's top thoroughbred riders yesterday in testifying about alleged race-fixing at New York tracks in the mid-1970's.
headline_main: Amy Implicates Leading jockeys in Trial; Lists Efforts to Fix Races Asked About Cordern Sl,500 Per Race The 'Fix' Method Jockeys Implicated Saratoga Race Cited 2 Men Convicted In Fix Scheme Islanders Scoring

abstract: The opening witness in the trial of Con Errico, the 58-year-old former jockey who has been charged with bribing jockeys to fix races at New York thoroughbred tracks, testified yesterday in Brooklyn Federal Court that he had rejected a bribe offer by Errico.
headline_main: Two Jockeys Testify On Bribes by Errico; Two Jockeys Testify on Errico Bribe Offers
headline_print_headline: Two Jockeys Testify On Bribes by Errico; Two Jockeys Testify on Errico Bribe Offers

abstract: ATLANTA, May 11 (UPI) Pam Higgins shot a three-under-par 70 today to win the Atlanta stop on the Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour by three strokes.

DALLAS, May 10 (UPI)--Tom Watson scrambled through the wind today, shot an even-par 70 that put him one stroke ahead of Curtis Strange and set up what he called a "head to head" 36hole finale in the rain-delayed Byron Nelson golf tournament.
headline_main: Watson Leads by a Shot in Dallas on 70-134; New Grouping System Third Birdie on 14th Misses Alcott and Higgins Tied

abstract: Christ Church (interdenominational) in Summit, N.J., was the setting yesterday for the marriage of Wendy Snead Stifel, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Henry G. Stifel of Short Hills, N.J., to George Christian Hansen, son of Mr. and Mrs. Burton D. Hansen of Moline, Ill. The Rev. Allen A. Tinker, a BaptistCongregational minister, performed the ceremony.
headline_main: Wendy S. Stifel Married in Jersey To George Hansen
